        <abstract> 
<p>Sends quotation from Armand Trousseau, <hi rend="italic">Lectures on clinical medicine</hi> [1868–72] 5: 213, on interruption of menstruation in young girls upon changing schools, as an example of the effect of changed conditions of life.</p> 
